316
00:22:41.402 --> 00:22:42.312
Now, now, a little.

317
00:22:42.319 --> 00:22:43.729
- No, no.
- Okay, baby,

318
00:22:43.737 --> 00:22:44.852
let's float it out there.

319
00:22:44.864 --> 00:22:46.104
- Let's go.
- Okay, okay.

320
00:22:46.115 --> 00:22:48.697
(all hollering)

321
00:22:53.497 --> 00:22:56.204
(birds chirping)

322
00:23:00.671 --> 00:23:03.670
Now, if you were a flavor of ice cream
what would it be?

324
00:23:03.674 --> 00:23:04.538
(water trickling)

325
00:23:04.550 --> 00:23:06.791
Rocky roll.
(al laughing)

326
00:23:06.802 --> 00:23:11.341
Hey!
(water splashes)

327
00:23:11.348 --> 00:23:14.385
(ominous music)
(leaves rustling)

328
00:23:14.393 --> 00:23:19.353
(muffled talking)
(water splashing)

329
00:23:21.567 --> 00:23:24.274
What's that vitamin C
stuff do for you anyway?

330
00:23:24.278 --> 00:23:27.486
Vitamin C's supposed to neutralize
the nitrates or something.

332
00:23:30.075 --> 00:23:32.532
[Marcie] What's the
matter? You see something?

333
00:23:32.536 --> 00:23:35.152
(Ioons calling)

334
00:23:36.415 --> 00:23:37.450
No, no, no.

335
00:23:40.127 --> 00:23:42.163
(Brenda shrieks)

336
00:23:42.171 --> 00:23:43.786
- Ned!
- Here we go.

337
00:23:43.797 --> 00:23:45.958
[Brenda] Get outta here!

338
00:23:48.218 --> 00:23:50.459
[Ned] Brenda, I'm getting to you.

339
00:23:50.471 --> 00:23:51.677
Very slowly.

340
00:23:51.680 --> 00:23:54.296
[Brenda] (laughs) You, you!

341
00:23:54.308 --> 00:23:57.050
[Marcie] Hey, you guys.
You ready to go back to work?

342
00:23:57.061 --> 00:23:58.471
- Yeah.

343
00:23:58.479 --> 00:24:00.720
(birds chirping)
- Oh, oh.

344
00:24:01.649 --> 00:24:05.224
- Come on, Alice.
- Help! Help!

346
00:24:05.235 --> 00:24:09.979
- Something's wrong with Ned.
Get a life preserver.

348
00:24:09.990 --> 00:24:12.356
(clattering)

349
00:24:14.078 --> 00:24:16.820
(water splashing)

350
00:24:20.417 --> 00:24:22.578
- Here.
- Help!

352
00:24:27.508 --> 00:24:30.045
- Jeez, where is he? Did he swim?
- I don't know, he's not here.

354
00:24:30.052 --> 00:24:32.885
He was around right around here somewhere.

355
00:24:32.888 --> 00:24:34.674
Go ahead, dive for him.

356
00:24:34.682 --> 00:24:37.173
(water splashing)

357
00:24:37.184 --> 00:24:38.390
- There he is.
- Right there he is.

358
00:24:38.394 --> 00:24:41.136
- Come on, you guys, help me.
- Watch his head.

359
00:24:41.146 --> 00:24:42.511
- Here.
- Hang on.

360
00:24:42.523 --> 00:24:43.603
- [Alice] Grab, pull it out.

361
00:24:43.607 --> 00:24:45.222
- Okay.
- Hurry up.

362
00:24:45.234 --> 00:24:47.190
Move it away.
(water splashing)

363
00:24:47.194 --> 00:24:48.684
- Hold him.
- Watch his head.

364
00:24:48.696 --> 00:24:50.232
- I got him.
- Here.

365
00:24:52.032 --> 00:24:54.569
(Ned coughing)

366
00:24:56.745 --> 00:24:58.360
- Can you give mouth-to-mouth?
- Yeah.

367
00:24:58.372 --> 00:25:00.200
- Pull up his head.
- Come on.

369
00:25:01.500 --> 00:25:05.084
(heavy breathing)

370
00:25:05.087 --> 00:25:06.793
- Oh god, is he all right?
- Come on, Ned.

371
00:25:06.797 --> 00:25:08.003
- Hurry up, hurry up.
- Come on, Ned.

372
00:25:08.007 --> 00:25:10.123
- Come on.
- Oh, Ned!

373
00:25:10.134 --> 00:25:11.749
Oh, Jesus!
(all yelling)

374
00:25:11.760 --> 00:25:14.422
(everyone hollering over each other)

375
00:25:17.683 --> 00:25:19.093
[Ned] Sorry!

376
00:25:19.101 --> 00:25:20.762
I'm sorry, all right?

377
00:25:22.771 --> 00:25:25.183
(bird cawing)

378
00:25:25.190 --> 00:25:27.852
(birds chirping)

379
00:25:29.445 --> 00:25:32.152
(Alice sighs)

380
00:25:32.156 --> 00:25:34.943
(drawer rattling)

381
00:25:42.249 --> 00:25:45.207
(suspenseful music)

382
00:25:46.628 --> 00:25:51.588
(dramatic music)
(Alice shrieks)

383
00:25:53.218 --> 00:25:55.200
(door squeaks)
Bill!

384
00:25:55.750 --> 00:25:57.298
Bill!

385
00:25:57.306 --> 00:25:59.888
Come here, quick!
Hurry!

387
00:25:59.892 --> 00:26:02.679
(ground rustling)

388
00:26:04.396 --> 00:26:08.438
- What is it?
- There's a snake over there.

390
00:26:08.442 --> 00:26:09.227
Where?

391
00:26:16.867 --> 00:26:18.607
What do I do?

392
00:26:19.912 --> 00:26:22.615
- It might bite.
- Haven't you ever been in the woods?

394
00:26:22.623 --> 00:26:24.033
We're not in the woods!

395
00:26:25.375 --> 00:26:27.199
- Jesus, Bill, what are you doing?
- There's a snake in here.

397
00:26:27.211 --> 00:26:30.544
- Then why are we in here?
- Whoa, feet don't fail me now!

399
00:26:30.547 --> 00:26:34.836
There it is!
(all screaming)

400
00:26:34.843 --> 00:26:36.708
[Marcie] I can't sleep
with a snake in here.

401
00:26:36.720 --> 00:26:38.506
[Brenda] Nobody told
us anything about snakes.

402
00:26:38.514 --> 00:26:40.095
- KiII it!

403
00:26:40.099 --> 00:26:41.179
- [Ned] You heard the lady.

404
00:26:41.183 --> 00:26:44.137
- I can't get it til it comes out.
- Well, call him.

406
00:26:44.144 --> 00:26:45.680
- How do you call a snake?

407
00:26:45.687 --> 00:26:49.100
- I'II flush it out!
(all screaming)

408
00:26:50.025 --> 00:26:53.483
(all screaming)

409
00:26:53.487 --> 00:26:55.102
[Jack] I got it.

410
00:26:55.114 --> 00:26:56.570
- Where?
- I got him.

411
00:26:56.573 --> 00:27:01.237
I got him.
(metal clanging)

412
00:27:01.245 --> 00:27:04.112
(thudding)
Oh god.

413
00:27:08.252 --> 00:27:13.086
- Is it dead?
- Either that or its got a very short clone.

415
00:27:13.090 --> 00:27:15.172
(girl scoffs)
Oh god.

416
00:27:15.175 --> 00:27:18.258
Well, at least we
know what's for dinner.

417
00:27:18.262 --> 00:27:19.547
- Oh.
- Marcie!

418
00:27:19.555 --> 00:27:21.341
- Gross.
- So sick.

419
00:27:21.348 --> 00:27:23.634
God.
(all laughing)

420
00:27:23.642 --> 00:27:24.757
(bird cawing)

421
00:27:24.768 --> 00:27:27.013
[Brenda] I'm making salad, do you want me
to go ahead and make some for everybody?

423
00:27:27.020 --> 00:27:28.226
Oh, that'd be great.

424
00:27:28.230 --> 00:27:29.595
I think we've got some
hamburger in there, too.

425
00:27:29.606 --> 00:27:32.147
- None for me, thank you.
- But there are apples.

427
00:27:32.151 --> 00:27:34.983
- Do you know how to make apple pie?
- Oh, sure, no sweat.

429
00:27:34.987 --> 00:27:36.773
(engine rumbling)
Whoa, what is going on?

430
00:27:36.780 --> 00:27:39.442
(Ned hollering)

431
00:27:47.207 --> 00:27:48.207
Oh shit.

432
00:27:51.253 --> 00:27:53.251
- All right, who are you people?
- Camp counselors.

434
00:27:53.255 --> 00:27:55.712
- Uh, Neddy's just fooling around.
- Yeah, right, I'm just fooling around.

436
00:27:55.716 --> 00:27:58.172
Hey, can it, goat cheese.
Steve Christy hire you people?

438
00:27:58.177 --> 00:27:59.007
(Brenda hums)

439
00:27:59.011 --> 00:27:59.796
He pay you for this?

440
00:27:59.803 --> 00:28:00.633
- Yeah.
- Hey, nice bike.

441
00:28:00.637 --> 00:28:03.670
- Have you been smoking, boy?
- Smoking? Don't smoke.

443
00:28:03.682 --> 00:28:05.092
Causes cancer.
You know what I mean.

444
00:28:05.100 --> 00:28:06.556
What, did you just get off
a space ship or something?

445
00:28:06.560 --> 00:28:09.347
Columbian gold, man.
Grass, hash, the weed.

446
00:28:10.272 --> 00:28:12.641
Hey, what's he talking about?
Hey, don't get smart.

448
00:28:12.649 --> 00:28:14.355
[Ned] Me? I'm as dumb as they come.

449
00:28:14.359 --> 00:28:16.771
Hey, not another word
outta you, you understand me?

450
00:28:16.778 --> 00:28:17.608
- Officer.
- Sure, officer.

451
00:28:17.613 --> 00:28:19.353
- Really, nothing's going on here.

452
00:28:19.364 --> 00:28:21.897
- We're just trying to get the place in shape.
- In shape for what?

454
00:28:21.909 --> 00:28:24.900
- Officer, is there anything we can do to help?
- We'd be glad to help out.

456
00:28:24.912 --> 00:28:26.118
Looking for somebody.

457
00:28:26.121 --> 00:28:29.909
- Now who's that?
- A guy named Ralph. The town crazy.

459
00:28:29.917 --> 00:28:32.408
Well, there's no crazy
people around here, right?

460
00:28:33.420 --> 00:28:35.035
I told you to sit on it, Tonto.

461
00:28:36.340 --> 00:28:40.290
Now, I got word that Ralph was peddling
out this way spouting his gospel.

463
00:28:40.302 --> 00:28:42.880
Well, we haven't seen anybody here, officer.
Just us.

465
00:28:42.888 --> 00:28:45.846
Uh, this guy Ralph, is he dangerous?

466
00:28:45.849 --> 00:28:48.511
Every time that loony gets
drunk he gets his call in.

467
00:28:48.518 --> 00:28:51.218
I end up spending the morning in court
and he gets a week in jail.

469
00:28:51.230 --> 00:28:53.312
(radio beeps)
Cycle 2, where are you?

470
00:28:53.315 --> 00:28:56.853
Come in, Cycle 2, Cycle 2.

471
00:28:56.860 --> 00:29:00.193
This is Dorf, I'm out here
at Camp Crystal Lake, over.

472
00:29:00.197 --> 00:29:01.232
[Dispatch] Pull it back in, Dorf.

473
00:29:01.240 --> 00:29:03.697
Chief wants you back
in town on the double.

474
00:29:03.700 --> 00:29:05.941
Roger that. 10-4, on my way, out.

475
00:29:08.622 --> 00:29:10.078
Never keep the chief waitin'.

476
00:29:13.460 --> 00:29:16.418
You kids keep your noses
clean, you understand?

477
00:29:16.421 --> 00:29:18.002
You'll be hearing from me if you don't.

478
00:29:22.135 --> 00:29:24.376
We ain't gonna stand for
no weirdness out here.

479
00:29:25.722 --> 00:29:30.682
(engine rumbling)
(muffled laughing)

480
00:29:49.162 --> 00:29:51.824
(metal clanging)

481
00:30:01.591 --> 00:30:04.207
(Alice humming)

482
00:30:05.470 --> 00:30:06.300
(dramatic music)
(Alice screams)

483
00:30:06.305 --> 00:30:10.048
(metal clattering)

484
00:30:10.058 --> 00:30:14.392
I'm a messenger of God.
You're doomed if you stay here.

486
00:30:17.983 --> 00:30:20.520
This place is cursed. Cursed.

487
00:30:23.447 --> 00:30:24.687
It's got a death curse.

488
00:30:25.991 --> 00:30:27.652
- Who are you?
- What do you want?

489
00:30:28.744 --> 00:30:32.194
- God sent me.
- Get outta here, man.

491
00:30:33.457 --> 00:30:36.740
I've got to warn you.
You're doomed if you stay.

493
00:30:38.628 --> 00:30:41.669
Go. Go!

495
00:30:46.386 --> 00:30:48.968
(door squeaks)

496
00:30:50.098 --> 00:30:52.430
(door thuds)

497
00:30:54.061 --> 00:30:57.140
- I think we just met Ralph.
- God, what's next?

499
00:30:58.690 --> 00:31:00.646
(Marcie sighs)

500
00:31:00.650 --> 00:31:03.483
(eerie music)

501
00:31:03.487 --> 00:31:06.024
(door squeaks)

502
00:31:09.034 --> 00:31:11.867
You're doomed. You're all doomed.

503
00:31:13.580 --> 00:31:18.540
(bike rattles)
(eerie music)

504
00:31:25.884 --> 00:31:30.844
(door squeaks)
(door thuds)

505
00:31:39.022 --> 00:31:40.637
- Who likes 'em rare?
- Me!

506
00:31:40.649 --> 00:31:43.853
How can you guys eat that stuff?
It looks like dead animals.

508
00:31:43.860 --> 00:31:47.565
Dead animals? That's the old counselors.
You cannibal.

510
00:31:47.572 --> 00:31:50.689
If you would mix all this stuff right
you would get all the protein you need.

512
00:31:50.700 --> 00:31:53.157
Too bad Annie never showed up,
she was supposed to be quite a good cook.

514
00:31:53.161 --> 00:31:55.489
Yeah, well don't expect me
to play chef for you guys.

516
00:31:55.497 --> 00:31:57.158
Uh oh, the squaws are revolting.

517
00:31:58.250 --> 00:32:01.242
- Trouble?
- Yeah, bad bulb or no power.

518
00:32:01.253 --> 00:32:02.413
Seems a little gloomy in here.

519
00:32:02.421 --> 00:32:05.336
- Hang on.
- Steve taught me how to use the emergency generator.

521
00:32:05.340 --> 00:32:08.047
The town power lines are
supposed to be real lousy.

522
00:32:08.051 --> 00:32:10.258
- Don't you love that macho talk?

523
00:32:10.262 --> 00:32:12.218
Emergency generator.

524
00:32:12.222 --> 00:32:14.133
- Like I haven't.
- Yeah, let's go.

525
00:32:14.141 --> 00:32:15.347
- Wait for me.
- I'll take care of this.

526
00:32:15.350 --> 00:32:18.099
- Neddy, can you watch the burners?
- Sure.

528
00:32:18.103 --> 00:32:18.933
- [Alice] Burner.

529
00:32:20.230 --> 00:32:23.814
- Wanna do this?
- Yeah.

530
00:32:23.817 --> 00:32:27.692
- You really think he's gonna be bent outta shape?
- I don't know.

532
00:32:27.696 --> 00:32:30.395
Hey, this looks almost like the one
at my uncle's cabin in Maine.

534
00:32:31.700 --> 00:32:34.649
- Well, here goes.
- What an antique.

536
00:32:34.661 --> 00:32:36.572
Okay.
(metal clangs)

537
00:32:36.580 --> 00:32:39.572
(generator rumbling)

538
00:32:43.628 --> 00:32:45.414
What has gone wrong?

539
00:32:49.593 --> 00:32:53.802
(birds chirping)
(bugs trilling)

540
00:32:53.805 --> 00:32:56.888
(bird cawing)

541
00:32:56.892 --> 00:32:59.679
(water trickling)

542
00:33:05.650 --> 00:33:08.437
(muffled talking)

543
00:33:09.446 --> 00:33:12.313
"Da da da da"
No.

544
00:33:13.783 --> 00:33:16.069
(muffled talking)

545
00:33:16.077 --> 00:33:18.568
(birds cawing)

546
00:33:34.638 --> 00:33:37.425
(ground rustling)

547
00:33:45.315 --> 00:33:47.931
(Ned whistling)

548
00:33:57.244 --> 00:33:59.610
(light dramatic music)

549
00:33:59.621 --> 00:34:02.237
(wood creaking)

550
00:34:03.333 --> 00:34:04.333
Hello?

551
00:34:10.840 --> 00:34:14.424
(suspenseful music)

552
00:34:14.427 --> 00:34:15.257
Can I help you?

553
00:34:18.181 --> 00:34:20.797
(Ioons calling)

554
00:34:23.103 --> 00:34:25.598
Hello? Hello?

556
00:34:27.983 --> 00:34:29.018
[Marcie] Come on.

557
00:34:29.025 --> 00:34:29.810
I'm coming, I'm coming.

558
00:34:33.780 --> 00:34:35.691
Woo, wind's come up.

559
00:34:35.699 --> 00:34:41.614
Shifted a good 180 degrees.
Guess I'll have to hold onto you.

561
00:34:41.621 --> 00:34:44.237
(lips smacking)

562
00:34:45.292 --> 00:34:48.036
- What about Ned?
- I don't love Ned.

564
00:34:48.044 --> 00:34:51.832
(scoffs)
He keeps acting like such a jerk.

565
00:34:51.840 --> 00:34:54.505
- Neddy! (thunder rumbling)
- Don't call him.

567
00:34:54.509 --> 00:34:57.459
I thought you wanted to give him one
of your motherly lectures.

569
00:34:57.470 --> 00:35:00.553
Look, Neddy's gonna do whatever
Neddy wants to do, ya know?

570
00:35:00.557 --> 00:35:02.297
(thunder rumbling)

571
00:35:02.309 --> 00:35:07.056
Ooh, it's gonna storm. Can tear down
that valley like a son of a gun.

573
00:35:07.063 --> 00:35:09.684
I've been afraid of storms
ever since I was a little kid.

575
00:35:09.691 --> 00:35:12.228
No. Really?
(Marcie laughs)

576
00:35:12.235 --> 00:35:14.851
Yeah, I've had this dream
about five or six times

577
00:35:14.863 --> 00:35:19.569
where I'm in a thunder storm
and it's raining really hard.

579
00:35:21.536 --> 00:35:24.494
It sounds like pebbles
when it hits the ground.

580
00:35:24.497 --> 00:35:25.361
I can hear it.

581
00:35:26.791 --> 00:35:29.123
I try to block out the sound with my hands

582
00:35:29.127 --> 00:35:32.289
only it doesn't work, it just
keeps getting louder and louder.

584
00:35:34.591 --> 00:35:38.004
And then the rain turns to blood

585
00:35:40.347 --> 00:35:44.215
and the blood washes
away in little rivers.

586
00:35:46.311 --> 00:35:48.017
Then the sound stops.

587
00:35:50.899 --> 00:35:53.853
- It's just a dream.
- Yeah, I know.

589
00:35:53.860 --> 00:35:57.603
I call it my shower dream.
(Jack laughs)

590
00:35:57.614 --> 00:36:00.860
- Hey, hey, this is no dream.
- Come on, we're gonna get soaked.

592
00:36:02.619 --> 00:36:06.658
(thunder rumbling)
(rain pattering)

593
00:36:06.665 --> 00:36:09.407
(wind whistling)

594
00:36:16.800 --> 00:36:20.258
(thunder booming)

595
00:36:20.261 --> 00:36:23.048
(water trickling)

